'''ЕҢnutehime''' (еӨ§йҮҺжүӢжҜ”еЈІ) is a {{ill|kami|ja|зҘһ (зҘһйҒ“)|12=draft}} mentioned in Japanese mythology.

== Overview ==

In the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|еҸӨдәӢиЁҳ|12=draft}}, ЕҢnutehime appears as another name for {{ill|ShЕҚdoshima|ja|е°ҸиұҶеі¶|12=draft}} during the {{ill|Kuniumi|ja|еӣҪз”ЈгҒҝ|12=draft}}. Additionally, the genealogical text {{ill|Shokeifu|ja|и«ёзі»иӯң|12=draft}} identifies her as the daughter of Furutama-no-Mikoto and another name for Himuka-no-Kamudomi-no-Mioya-Hime, the wife of Amanohikata-no-Mikoto.<ref>Nakada Norinobu, "Owari clan," in *Shokeifu*, vol. 2.</ref>

On ShЕҚdoshima, ЕҢnutehime is revered as the island's {{ill|Kunitama|ja|еі¶зҺүзҘһ|12=draft}} (spirit of the land). Historically, the island also had place names like ЕҢde-mura, reflecting her worship. The term "nute" or "nutehime" refers to a {{ill|dotaku|ja|йҠ…йҗё|12=draft}}, a type of ancient bronze bell. Notably, a dotaku was excavated from the western side of MitsugorЕҚ Pond.

== Genealogy ==

In the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|еҸӨдәӢиЁҳ|12=draft}}, ЕҢnutehime is described as the child of Izanagi and Izanami. There are no accounts of her having a consort or descendants.

=== Alternate Theory by HЕҚga Toshio ===

HЕҚga Toshio proposed that her husband might be related to Amanohikata-no-Mikoto, though genealogical traditions often contain discrepancies. He argued that ЕҢnutehime and her supposed consort are likely connected to the ancestors of the {{ill|Funi-kawachi-no-Kuni-no-Miyatsuko|ja|еҮЎжІіеҶ…еӣҪйҖ |12=draft}}, including Hiko-mikoso-no-Mikoto and his wife, based on her worship in Kawachi Province. The deity names, such as "IgatЕҚ," imply thunder ("Ikatsu").<ref>HЕҚga Toshio, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/hitori/kagami1.htm Dotaku and the Mirror Makers: Dotaku and the Mononobe clan]," in *Kojiki Chronicles*, 2014.</ref>

