== Overview ==

In the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|еҸӨдәӢиЁҳ|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, ЕҢnutehime appears as another name for {{ill|ShЕҚdoshima|ja|е°ҸиұҶеі¶|qq=draft|qq=draft}} during the {{ill|Kuniumi|ja|еӣҪз”ЈгҒҝ|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Additionally, the genealogical text {{ill|Shokeifu|ja|и«ёзі»иӯң|qq=draft|qq=draft}} identifies her as the daughter of Furutama-no-Mikoto and another name for Himuka-no-Kamudomi-no-Mioya-Hime, the wife of Amanohikata-no-Mikoto.<ref>Nakada Norinobu, "Owari clan," in *Shokeifu*, vol. 2.</ref>

On ShЕҚdoshima, ЕҢnutehime is revered as the island's {{ill|Kunitama|ja|еі¶зҺүзҘһ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (spirit of the land). Historically, the island also had place names like ЕҢde-mura, reflecting her worship. The term "nute" or "nutehime" refers to a {{ill|dotaku|ja|йҠ…йҗё|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a type of ancient bronze bell. Notably, a dotaku was excavated from the western side of MitsugorЕҚ Pond.

